FACTORIAL OF A NUMBER

AIM:
To find the factorial of a number by using PL/SQL

ALGORITHM:
Step1: Start
Step2: Declare the variables f and n as integer
Step3: Read the value of variable n
Step4: f:=1
Step5: Repeat the steps for each i given 1 to n
Step6: f:=f*i
Step7: End loop
Step8: Print the value of f
Step9: Stop


CODE

DECLARE

N INTEGER;
F INTEGER;
I INTEGER;

BEGIN
N:=&N;
F:=1;
FOR I IN 1..N LOOP
F:=F*I;
END LOOP;
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(F);
END;
/
